You will generate an API reference for a components props.

- Reference `src/lib/components/docs/api-reference/components/avatar-group-api.ts` for an example implementation
- Reference `src/lib/components/docs/api-reference/api-reference.ts` for the documentation apis
- Components can be found under `src/lib/components/ui/{{component}}`
- You can tell a component prop is bindable because when it is destructured from the `$props()` function it will be assigned to `$bindable`.

To generate an API reference for a component you will need to modify a few files:

1. Create the `{{component}}-api.ts` file under `src/lib/components/docs/api-reference/components`.
2. Add the re-export to the `index.ts` file in the same directory 
example:
```ts
export { components as ButtonReference } from './button-api';
```
3. Add the `APIReference` component to the components documentation page located at `src/routes/components/{{component}}`
```diff
<script>
+   import ApiReference from '$lib/components/docs/api-reference/api-reference.svelte';
+	import { ButtonReference } from '$lib/components/docs/api-reference/components';
// ...
</script>

<!-- ... -->
+<ApiReference name="Button" components={ButtonReference} />
```
- If there is an acknoledgements section place the reference above it

- DO NOT create new types 
- If all props from a component come from another component they can be forwarded to the documentation for that component if you don't know where to forward them ask

